          "rationale": "Texas law requires a person who operates a continuous-airflow inflatable amusement ride (bounce house, inflatable slide) to carry a combined single limit liability policy of not less than $1,000,000 per occurrence, written by a Texas-authorized insurer (Tex. Occ. Code 2151.1012). This inflatable-specific minimum controls over the general Class B floor; a certified copy of the policy is filed with the Texas Department of Insurance.",
